President Donald J. Trump has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the Inauguration of President Volodymyr Zelenskyy of Ukraine. The delegation will be led by Secretary of the Department of Energy, Rick Perry, and includes United States Special Representative for Ukraine Negotiations, Kurt Volker, United States Ambassador to the European Union, Gordon D. Sondland, Director for European Affairs at the National Security Council, Alexander Vindman, and Acting Deputy Chief of Mission for the United States Embassy in Ukraine, Joseph Pennington. The Inauguration will take place on May 20, 2019, in Kyiv, Ukraine.